WEBVTT

00:20.689 --> 00:24.442
BABYFACE: Okay, boys, grab the loot.
And maybe a couple of those suckers too.

00:25.902 --> 00:28.822
PLASTIC MAN:
Not so fast, Babyface.

00:30.365 --> 00:34.119
You've been caught
by the long arms of the law.

00:36.121 --> 00:38.957
Well, if it isn't Plastic Man and, uh...

00:39.207 --> 00:40.750
Uh, and, uh..

00:41.126 --> 00:44.212
Elongated Man.
You know, the ductile detective?

00:44.462 --> 00:46.339
Uh, never heard of you.

00:51.428 --> 00:52.804
I just don't get it.

00:53.054 --> 00:55.557
I'm more professional,
the better detective...

00:55.557 --> 00:57.809
...and yet the public prefers you.

00:58.518 --> 01:02.397
Ooh, not just public, my D-list
doppelganger. Batman too.

01:04.566 --> 01:05.900
[MAN GRUNTS]

01:06.151 --> 01:09.446
Oh, yeah. The Caped Crusader
prefers to work with moi.

01:09.446 --> 01:13.575
Please. The Dark Knight only turns to you
when I'm on another case...

01:14.242 --> 01:17.370
...and then, only as a last resort.

01:20.540 --> 01:21.541
[GASPS]

01:21.791 --> 01:25.003
Dude, you're delusional.
Bats and I are best buds.

01:25.253 --> 01:27.756
We hang out even when there's no evil
doing to be undone.

01:28.048 --> 01:29.340
[GRUNTS]

01:30.842 --> 01:32.469
[GRUNTS]

01:34.304 --> 01:35.263
[SIGHS]

01:43.563 --> 01:48.651
I would think Batman prefers a partner
who doesn't pilfer criminal proceeds.

01:49.027 --> 01:50.528
Low blow, highbrow.

01:50.528 --> 01:52.280
[FOOTSTEPS NEARBY]

01:55.366 --> 01:57.077
[BOTH GRUNT]

02:05.752 --> 02:07.337
[BOTH SCREAM]

02:09.464 --> 02:13.009
BABYFACE: That taffy puller should keep
you wrapped up for a while, see?

02:13.843 --> 02:15.386
This kind of incompetence...

02:15.637 --> 02:19.349
...is exactly why Batman
always chooses me.

02:19.599 --> 02:22.352
He'd rather work with me
any day of the week.

02:31.736 --> 02:34.823
Truth be told, between the two of you...

02:35.490 --> 02:37.659
...I prefer to work alone.

03:16.656 --> 03:19.450
[MACHINE POWERING UP]

03:21.911 --> 03:23.997
[MACHINE WHIRRING]

03:25.290 --> 03:27.792
Five months of careful research...

03:27.792 --> 03:30.920
...to culminate
in this one magnificent moment.

03:31.171 --> 03:33.423
[PHONE RINGING]

03:40.722 --> 03:41.723
Dr. Choi, hello?

03:42.015 --> 03:43.725
AQUAMAN [OVER PHONE] :
Doctor, Aquaman here.

03:44.017 --> 03:47.270
- What's new, old friend?
- I was just in the middle of conducting...

03:47.520 --> 03:50.815
...a delicate tachyon-detection experiment,
old friend.

03:51.107 --> 03:53.818
Tachyons, eh? Splendid. Attaboy.

03:54.068 --> 03:55.945
Get to the point.

03:56.196 --> 03:59.699
I'm calling about Batman.
He's-- How shall I put this?

04:00.325 --> 04:02.410
--Shipping a bit of bilge.

04:02.994 --> 04:04.078
Describe the bilge.

04:04.871 --> 04:07.790
We were fighting
that toxic torment Chemo...

04:07.790 --> 04:10.084
...and the Caped Crusader...

04:10.752 --> 04:12.295
Well, he took one in the face.

04:12.921 --> 04:13.671
I'll be right there.

04:30.521 --> 04:31.773
- Outrageous.
- Ugh.

04:31.773 --> 04:33.066
What miracle is this?

04:33.316 --> 04:36.236
As the Atom, I can shrink
to the size of a subatomic particle...

04:36.486 --> 04:38.571
...and ride electrons
along the phone wires.

04:39.280 --> 04:40.281
Do it again.

04:40.531 --> 04:42.408
[BATMAN COUGHING]

04:43.743 --> 04:44.744
Oh; my'

04:47.080 --> 04:49.332
You don't look well at all.
Open wide for me.

04:55.171 --> 04:57.090
Silicon-based microorganisms?

04:57.382 --> 05:00.718
Specifically, fast-replicating,
monoclinic phyllosilicates.

05:01.135 --> 05:04.681
What kind of medicine shall we prescribe,
doc?

05:04.931 --> 05:07.976
You don't know what kind of doctor I am,
do you?

05:07.976 --> 05:10.812
A hero doctor, through and through.

05:10.812 --> 05:12.230
A physicist.

05:12.480 --> 05:15.900
And this goes beyond medicine.
Batman's cells are mutating.

05:15.900 --> 05:18.820
Before long, they'll overwhelm
his central nervous system...

05:18.820 --> 05:22.740
...causing a loss of motor control,
then paralysis, and finally...

05:23.032 --> 05:24.867
Then we don't have much time.

05:24.867 --> 05:28.913
Chemo's headed out to sea,
straight for the Bialyian nuclear test site.

05:28.913 --> 05:32.125
Forget Chemo, old chum.
The Navy can handle him.

05:32.375 --> 05:36.754
He's right. The only way to halt this process
is for me to go into your body...

05:37.005 --> 05:38.965
...and destroy the organisms myself.

05:38.965 --> 05:40.466
Sounds like an adventure.

05:40.717 --> 05:43.177
Think you might need
a strong swimmer along?

05:43.428 --> 05:45.221
One with the heart of a beluga whale?

05:45.805 --> 05:48.850
- Oh, I don't think--
- Take him, you'll need the muscle.

05:49.100 --> 05:50.435
Oh...

05:50.685 --> 05:53.438
Then promise me
you won't do anything foolish.

05:53.688 --> 05:56.441
Activity makes the
virus spread faster, okay?

05:57.233 --> 05:58.985
[CHEMO GROWLS]

05:59.902 --> 06:04.073
Say "ah." and remember, stay put.

06:05.199 --> 06:07.160
Ah...

06:08.619 --> 06:09.871
I thought they'd never leave.

06:10.121 --> 06:11.122
[GRUNTS]

06:18.921 --> 06:20.214
The human lung.

06:20.465 --> 06:23.217
Mother Nature
is truly our greatest architect.

06:23.468 --> 06:26.346
Look, dendritic cells, alveoli--

06:26.721 --> 06:29.140
Yes, yes, all very interesting.

06:29.432 --> 06:31.351
But how small are we?

06:31.642 --> 06:33.269
ATOM:
About 15 microns.

06:33.519 --> 06:36.522
Small enough to slip
between Batman's cells without damage.

06:36.814 --> 06:39.901
And, uh, that's Batman's cilia
you're hanging from.

06:40.943 --> 06:42.487
Cilia and sillier.

06:42.737 --> 06:44.614
[LAUGHING]

06:45.073 --> 06:46.616
Alley-oop-

06:46.991 --> 06:48.076
[LAUGHING]

06:48.076 --> 06:49.202
[GRUNTS]

06:49.452 --> 06:52.580
You know, this can't help
but remind me of the time I ventured...

06:52.830 --> 06:56.000
...into the belly of a giant squid
to retrieve the enchanted pearl...

06:56.250 --> 06:58.586
...needed to save the Falkland Islands.

06:58.836 --> 07:02.423
Let's stay focused on the mission at hand,
shall we?

07:02.715 --> 07:04.509
Finding those silicon compounds?

07:05.093 --> 07:06.844
Yes, professor.

07:09.097 --> 07:12.058
BATMAN: My body grows weaker
with each passing moment.

07:12.934 --> 07:16.646
Only the thought of the destruction
that walking chemical spill will wreak...

07:16.896 --> 07:18.064
...keeps me focused.

07:44.173 --> 07:46.008
[GROWLING]

08:01.691 --> 08:04.068
[BATMAN GROANING]

08:06.362 --> 08:09.449
BATMAN:
Loss of motor control, check.

08:31.304 --> 08:33.097
COMPUTER:
Oxygen, low.

08:34.182 --> 08:36.767
Batmobile, switch to voice command.

08:37.226 --> 08:38.936
COMPUTER:
Voice command, active.

08:41.189 --> 08:42.857
Surface.

08:49.655 --> 08:53.034
As we travel through the villi,
the CP4 barium sonowave...

08:53.284 --> 08:56.370
...will indicate any monoclinic
phyllosilicates in our vicinity.

08:56.621 --> 08:58.789
English, man. English.

08:59.040 --> 09:00.082
[GRUNTS]

09:00.082 --> 09:06.547
This little doohickey beeps
when the cooties are near.

09:07.048 --> 09:09.550
Ah! Cooties, yes.

09:12.220 --> 09:13.054
[BEEPING]

09:13.304 --> 09:14.972
ATOM:
Okay, now we're cooking.

09:27.235 --> 09:32.406
These phyllosilicates are dangerous,
so let's think this out.

09:34.742 --> 09:37.912
En garde, you microscopic misanthrope.

09:43.376 --> 09:45.836
[LAUGHING]

09:46.087 --> 09:50.466
We shall call this adventure
the one where larger than life heroes...

09:50.758 --> 09:53.427
...come in small packages.

09:53.678 --> 09:55.054
Huh? Wha--?

09:56.639 --> 09:57.765
ATOM:
It's replicating.

09:58.266 --> 10:00.393
Yes, and it's making more of itself too.

10:00.643 --> 10:02.144
We'll just have to fight harder.

10:05.231 --> 10:06.941
[AQUAMAN GRUNTING]

10:09.735 --> 10:12.071
Now's the time for thinking, not fighting.

10:12.321 --> 10:16.784
Ha! The problem with you, Atom,
is that you think when you should feel.

10:17.326 --> 10:19.287
[SONOWAVE BEEPING]

10:23.416 --> 10:26.085
Time to try things my way.

10:29.589 --> 10:32.258
A simple electromagnetic shock
will destroy them...

10:32.258 --> 10:35.553
...and cure Batman in the process.
Observe.

10:47.189 --> 10:49.859
See? Thinking's not so tough.

10:50.109 --> 10:51.193
Maybe you should try it sometime.

10:51.444 --> 10:52.778
[BOTH GRUNT]

10:59.660 --> 11:02.496
There's no way
they could've spread this quickly unless--

11:02.747 --> 11:07.293
Unless Batman disregarded my orders
for bed rest and went after Chemo.

11:07.543 --> 11:11.047
Of course he went after Chemo.
He's Batman.

11:11.297 --> 11:13.257
[PHYLLOSILICATES GROWLING]

11:15.217 --> 11:18.638
Worry not, Poindexter.
I shall lead us to safer ground.

11:20.097 --> 11:24.226
Wait. At our size,
blood vessels are raging rivers of death.

11:24.477 --> 11:27.188
Not if I summon us a sturdy steed.

11:27.188 --> 11:29.231
And what exactly
are you going to summon?

11:29.523 --> 11:32.443
This is not the ocean.
There are no fish in Batman's--

11:33.194 --> 11:35.029
[LYMPHOCYTE SQUEAKING]

11:36.155 --> 11:37.114
I stand corrected.

11:40.368 --> 11:41.369
AQUAMAN:
Giddyup.

11:41.619 --> 11:42.620
[LYMPHOCYTE SQUEAKING]

12:00.221 --> 12:01.639
[CHEMO GROWLING]

12:05.226 --> 12:08.187
Evasive subroutine, two-niner, go.

12:13.651 --> 12:16.487
Concussive grenades, full power.

12:31.419 --> 12:32.878
[GROWLS]

12:37.550 --> 12:41.303
BATMAN: Let's hope Atom and Aquaman
are having better luck than I am.

12:41.929 --> 12:44.181
ATOM:
You're going to kill us.

12:44.432 --> 12:45.683
Have at thee.

12:45.933 --> 12:47.476
[GRUNTING]

12:48.018 --> 12:49.103
Huzzah!

12:49.353 --> 12:50.521
[ATOM GRUNTS]

12:50.771 --> 12:52.273
[PHYLLOSILICATE SHRIEKS]

12:55.901 --> 12:57.278
[AQUAMAN LAUGHING]

12:57.528 --> 13:00.114
AQUAMAN:
I'm king of the sea.

13:00.364 --> 13:02.658
ATOM:
Just get us out of here!

13:08.748 --> 13:10.166
[LYMPHOCYTE SQUEAKS]

13:14.253 --> 13:15.796
[ATOM SCREAMS]

13:18.466 --> 13:20.384
That was outrageous.

13:21.010 --> 13:22.762
I'll admit, we survived.

13:23.262 --> 13:24.430
[LYMPHOCYTE WHINNIES]

13:24.680 --> 13:27.683
Good boy. You were magnificent.

13:27.933 --> 13:30.853
Yes, big hug-

13:31.103 --> 13:34.231
He's not hugging you.
He is merely interpreting you...

13:34.482 --> 13:36.776
...as a foreign body
to be surrounded and destroyed.

13:37.026 --> 13:39.487
Sure feels like a hug to me...

13:39.487 --> 13:42.531
...and since we found you
in Batman's bloodstream...

13:42.823 --> 13:45.367
...I think we'll name you Platelet.

13:45.367 --> 13:48.871
- Except that's a lymphocyte.
- Platelet it is.

13:50.080 --> 13:51.832
[PHYLLOSILICATES GROWLING]

13:53.167 --> 13:56.337
AQUAMAN:
Neptune's beard. They're everywhere.

13:57.379 --> 13:59.298
And we're not going to beat them
head-on.

13:59.715 --> 14:01.926
Not the way you fight, no.

14:02.176 --> 14:05.387
Our only chance is to find
and destroy the seed cell.

14:05.638 --> 14:09.517
And based on these symptoms,
it can only be in one place.

14:09.517 --> 14:11.644
Batman's brain.

14:11.894 --> 14:13.854
Then let's ride.

14:15.147 --> 14:17.274
Hyah, Platelet, away!

14:27.243 --> 14:29.453
[CHEMO GROWLS]

14:52.393 --> 14:55.354
BATMAN: Chemo went to a lot of trouble
to get that nuke.

14:55.354 --> 14:58.065
But for whom is the question.

14:59.066 --> 15:02.361
Who's the real brain
behind this mindless brute?

15:04.071 --> 15:07.658
BRAIN:
You poor, pitiful fool, Batman.

15:07.908 --> 15:09.952
I believe this is checkmate.

15:10.327 --> 15:12.454
BATMAN:
The Brain, ironic.

15:12.454 --> 15:16.458
BRAIN: As much fun as it was
watching you match wits with Chemo...

15:16.917 --> 15:22.423
...our little toy is now going
where no one will get to it.

15:22.715 --> 15:26.719
And if the Bialyian people
do not surrender to my rule...

15:27.011 --> 15:31.098
...my lackey's corrosive juices
will eat through the bomb's housing...

15:31.348 --> 15:36.687
...causing an explosion
that will destroy their entire country.

15:36.937 --> 15:41.025
But before we get to that nasty business,
Batman...

15:41.442 --> 15:45.571
...I think it is time for Chemo
to put you out of your misery.

15:45.571 --> 15:46.614
[BATMAN GRUNTS]

15:50.200 --> 15:51.869
Eject.

16:07.468 --> 16:09.345
AQUAMAN:
Batman's brain.

16:09.595 --> 16:11.931
Is that the seed cell you spoke of?

16:12.181 --> 16:16.185
Yes.
This field pressurizer will obliterate it.

16:21.273 --> 16:23.233
[GROWLING]

16:26.570 --> 16:29.073
What in Davy Jones' Locker
is happening?

16:29.323 --> 16:32.326
They're mutating.
Growing bigger, stronger.

16:32.326 --> 16:36.163
It's as if Batman's been exposed
to Chemo's toxins all over again.

16:36.413 --> 16:38.832
Tell me you have a plan.

16:39.291 --> 16:41.001
[CHEMO GROWLING]

16:47.841 --> 16:49.343
[SCREAMING]

16:49.343 --> 16:51.387
[ROARS]

16:54.014 --> 16:58.519
BRAIN: Submit, you mindless plebeians.
Bow before the Brain.

17:04.149 --> 17:05.693
<i>Mac ANS]</i>

17:27.256 --> 17:29.216
[GROWLING]

17:34.138 --> 17:36.807
[BATMAN BREATHING HEAVILY]

17:47.484 --> 17:49.695
BATMAN:
And now for the Brain.

17:52.948 --> 17:56.160
Come on, doc,
write us a heroic prescription.

17:56.410 --> 17:58.162
L-- I don't know.

17:58.412 --> 18:02.458
Every course of action I can think of
leads to unacceptable consequences.

18:02.458 --> 18:06.211
Then this is not the time to think,
but the time to act.

18:07.212 --> 18:08.172
ATOM:
No.

18:08.422 --> 18:09.840
What are you doing?

18:10.132 --> 18:12.968
Drawing their forces
so you can destroy the seed cell.

18:13.218 --> 18:14.720
But you'll never survive.

18:15.012 --> 18:19.433
Perhaps.
But at least I'll have one heck of a story.

18:19.433 --> 18:20.768
[AQUAMAN SHOUTING]

18:23.353 --> 18:24.521
Huzzah!

18:27.232 --> 18:32.362
BRAIN:
Impossible. My plot was foolproof.

18:33.572 --> 18:35.115
[BATMAN GROANS]

18:35.365 --> 18:39.161
BRAIN: Batman.
- I'm taking you in.

18:39.411 --> 18:42.039
BRAIN:
A brave, but futile gesture, detective.

18:42.289 --> 18:47.377
The fast-replicating silicates Chemo
infected you with are going to kill you.

18:47.377 --> 18:51.006
Even now, you can barely stand.

18:52.466 --> 18:55.052
[BATMAN GROANS]

18:55.302 --> 18:57.429
[BATMAN BREATHING HEAVILY]

18:57.679 --> 19:00.432
So it comes down to this.

19:00.432 --> 19:04.561
Brain versus brawn,
mano y mano...

19:04.812 --> 19:07.314
...locked in mortal combat.

19:07.564 --> 19:09.775
[BRAIN GRUNTING]

19:15.405 --> 19:17.658
[AQUAMAN GRUNTING]

19:18.492 --> 19:19.451
Huh?

19:19.743 --> 19:20.702
[PLATELET SHRIEKS]

19:21.203 --> 19:23.080
Platelet!

19:23.413 --> 19:24.957
Now you've clone it.

19:25.207 --> 19:27.626
[ATOM SCREAMING]

19:28.710 --> 19:31.088
[ATOM GRUNTING]

19:39.471 --> 19:41.265
Outrageous.

19:41.515 --> 19:45.352
Evildoers, beware my wrath!

19:46.311 --> 19:49.273
- Uh, what about the plan?
- Blah, blah, blah!

19:49.523 --> 19:51.775
Let's punch them.

19:52.067 --> 19:53.402
[ATOM GRUNTING]

19:53.694 --> 19:54.903
[GRUNTS]

20:00.242 --> 20:02.202
[GROWLS]

20:24.349 --> 20:26.393
[PHYLLOSILICATES SHRIEKING]

20:37.487 --> 20:39.239
[BATMAN GROANING]

20:41.742 --> 20:42.826
[BRAIN LAUGHS]

20:43.076 --> 20:45.162
BRAIN:
Now who's the weakling?

20:45.412 --> 20:48.540
And so it ends.

20:53.128 --> 20:54.129
[BRAIN SHOUTS]

20:54.463 --> 20:55.505
[SPEAKING IN FRENCH]

20:55.797 --> 20:59.343
But Chemo's microorganisms
should have killed you.

20:59.885 --> 21:02.638
I've got microorganisms
of my own, Brain.

21:02.888 --> 21:04.640
And mine work for the good guys.

21:05.557 --> 21:07.726
Die, you fleshy fool.

21:16.526 --> 21:18.612
BATMAN:
Your mind is twisted, Brain.

21:18.612 --> 21:24.117
You can think about the error of your ways
while doing hard time in a Bialyian prison.

21:27.996 --> 21:32.709
I've not seen heroics like yours
since the time I saved an elderly merman...

21:33.001 --> 21:36.380
...from a pack of great whites.
Good show.

21:36.630 --> 21:42.219
But, you know, coming to my aid like that
was not the rational course of action, doc.

21:42.636 --> 21:46.473
Let's call it
a momentary lapse in judgment.

21:46.473 --> 21:51.228
Our victory though has come
at a great cost.

21:51.478 --> 21:54.982
- Ah, Platelet.
- I'm so sorry, Aquaman.

21:55.232 --> 21:57.317
He was a valiant steed.

21:57.567 --> 22:00.237
But lymphocytes never last long.

22:00.821 --> 22:05.826
Come then, let us honor Platelet
and live as heroes.

22:06.285 --> 22:08.578
Take us home, old chum.

22:09.621 --> 22:10.914
There's only one way out.

22:11.164 --> 22:13.458
Left at the jugular,
then on toward a tear duct.

22:13.709 --> 22:15.711
Tear duct? But surely...

22:16.670 --> 22:19.131
...Batman never cries.
